-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item using ROW_NUMBER
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_category.sql
```sql
-- Enrich order items with product category, handling nullable category_id
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity,
        oi.unit_price,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    order_id,
    product_id,
    quantity,
    unit_price,
    category_name
FROM source
```

-- models/marts/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        ic.category_name,
        ic.item_id,
        ic.quantity,
        r.return_id
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_category') }} ic
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = ic.item_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(CASE WHEN return_id IS NOT NULL THEN quantity ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
    ROUND(
        SUM(CASE WHEN return_id IS NOT NULL THEN quantity ELSE 0 END) * 1.0
        / SUM(quantity),
        4
    ) AS return_rate
FROM source
GROUP BY category_name
ORDER BY return_rate DESC
